Special Board Meeting Monday, July 27, 2020 at 6 PM

Monday, July 27, 2020, at 6 pmMondayâ€™s July 27, 2020 Board meeting will be livestreamed. The link to the livestream will be posted on the Districtâ€™s website at 5:45 PM on July 27, 2020.

If you would like to speak in person at the Board meeting on July 27, 2020, please complete this form https://bit.ly/2CTwucy. The Regular Board Meeting scheduled for Thursday, July 16, 2020, at 6 pm has been moved to online.

Per Governor Wolf's new restrictions starting 7/16/2020 which limits indoor gatherings to 25 people or less, the EYSD Board meeting will be closed to the public for in-person attendance. EYSD will livestream the meeting through YouTube. A link will be placed at the top of the districtâ€™s site at 5:45 pm, which will take you to the livestream.

As a member of the public, you will not be able to speak, via a remote method, at the meeting. However, if you wish to participate in the â€œHearing of the Patronsâ€ portions of the agenda, please forward your comments via email: boardmessage@easternyork.net or click on this link to submit a comment https://bit.ly/2Up1es5

post_text:
The Eastern York School District will continue to offer ALL EYSD students a free Grab-N-Go lunch and breakfast.

To participate, parents/guardians can drive through to the elementary school closest to their residence. Pick-up will be at the front of each school, from 11:00am until 1:00pm on Monday April 6, 2020, and Wednesday April 8, 2020. Each child will receive two breakfast bags and two lunch bags on Monday. On Wednesday three breakfast bags and three lunch bags will be provided.

Alternatively, students who can safely walk to the school can also pick up their lunch/breakfast.

District staff will be there to hand out food packages. Please be advised that today, Governor Wolf recommended that all Pennsylvanians wear a mask if they must leave their homes. Therefore, for the safety of all, staff handing out lunches will be wearing a mask and gloves. Thank you and be safe.

post_text:
The Eastern York School District will continue to offer ALL EYSD students a free Grab-N-Go lunch and breakfast. Meals will be available through the school closures caused by COVID-19.

To participate, parents/guardians can drive through to the elementary school closest to their residence. Pick-up will be at the front of each school, from 11:00am until 1:00pm on Monday March 30th , and Wednesday April and 1st. Each child will receive two breakfast bags and two lunch bags on Monday. On Wednesday three breakfast bags and three lunch bags will be provided.

Alternatively, students who can safely walk to the school can also pick up their lunch/breakfast. Food Services Department staff will be there to hand out food packages.
